When offering bones, players should use the bank chest near [[Camelot Castle]] in a [[PvP world]], which is the closest bank chest to a teleport. The chest is within a safe area from player killers. Equip a [[dust battlestaff]], and keep a [[tinderbox]] and [[law rune]]s in the inventory. Withdraw 24 bones and two [[marrentill]]s, teleport to the house, light the incense burners, and offer the bones at the gilded altar. Use each bone manually at the altar to speed up the process. Teleport back to Camelot and repeat.

Players who do not have the Construction level to build a gilded altar can look up for house party hosts. Currently, this takes place on World 330 at the [[Rimmington]] [[house portal]] and the [[Yanille]] house portal. If the host is in Rimmington, the player can take noted bones and unnote them by using them on [[Phials]] for 5 coins per note.

Experience rates vary depending on the type of bone used and performance. With good banking and accurate clicks, players can offer 2550 bones per hour, assuming the player uses each bone manually on the altar. This equates to around 1,340,000 experience per hour when using superior dragon bones, and 643,000 experience per hour when using dragon bones. The rates can be increased up to 3500 bones per hour if using alternative accounts to light the incense burners and bringing bones from the bank, or even higher if hiring runners. If the player is not manually using the bones on the altar, only up to 1070 bones per hour can be offered. 

More information about experience rates and costs can be seen [[Pay-to-play Prayer training#Experience rates and cost|below]]. Currently, offering superior dragon bones costs {{Coins|{{GEP|Superior dragon bones}}/525}} coins per experience, and dragon bones  {{Coins|{{GEP|Dragon bones}}/252}} coins per experience.

==Offering bones at the Chaos Altar==
[[File:Chaos Temple (hut).png|300px|right]]
Offering bones at the [[Chaos Temple (hut)|Chaos Temple]] in [[Multi-combat area|multi-combat]] level 38 [[Wilderness]] is a slightly slower but a lot cheaper alternative to the gilded altar. The temple has an altar which grants the same experience as a gilded altar with two burners lit, but also gives a 50% chance for the bone not to be consumed. This effectively doubles the amount of experience received per bone. However, using the altar comes at the risk of having to face [[Player killing|player killers]] who frequently like to hop between worlds at the location.

Players can take noted bones and un-note them at the [[Elder Chaos druid (NPC)|Elder Chaos druid]] just outside of the temple for 50 coins per note. While convenient, this also increases the amount that the player is risking to player killers. Players who wish to minimise risk can take only an inventory of unnoted bones at a time and suicide to bank for more bones.

The fastest way to get to the altar is to use [[Ghorrock Teleport]] (or the respective house portal) and run south. Players who do not have the Magic level to cast Ghorrock Teleport can use the respective [[Ghorrock teleport|teleport tablet]] instead.
*Alternatively, players who have an [[Obelisk (Construction)|Ancient Obelisk]] in their player-owned house and have completed hard tasks in the [[Wilderness Diary]] can use it to teleport to level 44 Wilderness and then run south.
*Another option is to use [[Cemetery Teleport]] on the [[Arceuus spellbook]] or the respective house portal and run north. This is a slightly slower method, but it has lower requirements.
*Using the [[burning amulet]] to the [[Lava Maze]] entrance and running south-west is not recommended, except for players using the suicide strategy below. The Lava Maze entrance is often crowded by player killers due to its proximity to [[Revenant Caves]] and [[King Black Dragon Lair]].

Experience rates vary depending on the bone used and the number of player killers. Players can expect to make around 2000 bone offers per hour when manually using the bones on the altar. This would equate to around 500,000 experience per hour using dragon or wyvern bones, and 1,050,000 experience per hour using superior dragon bones. At maximum efficiency and when uninterrupted, it is possible to gain up to 1,800,000 experience per hour when using superior dragon bones. Slightly higher rates can be achieved by using runners.

===Strategies===
As the altar can also be used to recharge Prayer points, players can keep Protect from Magic and Augury prayers up while offering bones and pray at the altar when needed.

====Planning to die====
