==Reanimating ensouled heads==
[[File:Ensouled dragon head detail.png|220x220px|right]]
Reanimating [[ensouled head]]s and killing the reanimated monsters near the [[Dark Altar]] is a relatively slow training method, but it requires less effort than manually offering bones at a gilded altar or the Chaos Altar. This method is mainly recommended for players who wish to save money on Prayer training and do not wish go to the [[Wilderness]], as offering bones at the Chaos Altar offers a lot faster experience and is usually comparable in terms of cost.

For this method, players must have at least 60% [[favour]] in [[Arceuus]]. Players will also need to have unlocked the fairy ring {{Fairycode|CIS}} for faster access to the Dark Altar, and a fast access to fairy rings, such as the [[Fairy ring (Construction)|fairy ring in the POH]], [[quest point cape]], or using the [[Salve Graveyard Teleport]]. Having the [[rune pouch]] is strongly recommended to save inventory space. It is also recommended to buy the ensouled heads in advance, as most of them have a low trade volumes on the Grand Exchange.

Experience rates vary depending on the type of ensouled head used and combat stats. With high combat stats, players can reanimate up to 220 ensouled heads per hour. This equates to around 343,000 experience per hour when reanimating [[ensouled dragon head]]s. Higher rates can be achieved by using a cannon to kill the reanimated monsters faster, but this makes the method slightly more expensive. Players will also gain some passive combat and Magic experience from this method.

More information about experience rates and costs can be seen [[Pay-to-play Prayer training#Experience rates and cost|below]]. Currently, reanimating ensouled dragon heads costs {{Coins|-({{GEP|Ensouled dragon head}}+{{GEP|Blood rune}}*2+{{GEP|Nature rune}}*4+{{GEP|Soul rune}}*4) / 1560 round 2}} coins per experience.

